   First Gov site A National Agenda for Nursing Workforce Racial/Ethnic
   Diversity
   Report discusses the need to have a culturally diverse workforce in
   order to meet our Nation's health care needs and issues related to
   racial/ethnic diversity in nursing education and practice. It presents
   goals and actions that can serve as national agenda to address those
   issues.

   The Health Care Workforce in Ten States: Education, Practice and
   Policy: Interstate Comparison
   Report summarizes the health workforce data, available resources and
   description of the extent the state invests in collecting health
   workforce data. Describes various issues and influences affecting the
   health workforce, including the state's legislative and regulatory
   history and its current programs. Assesses the state's internal
   capacity and existing strategies for addressing the workforce issues
   and influences. Analyzes the policy implications of the state's current
   workforce, issues, capacity, and strategies.

   State Health Workforce Profiles--Interested in finding data on the
   supply, demand, and use of health personnel? State Health Workforce
   Profiles offer accurate and current data on health care employment.
   Profiles also contain comparisons with other states and overviews of
   residents' health status and health services that influence supply of
   and demand for health workers.
   The MCH Training Program: An Evaluation
   This publication focuses on the MCH Training programs, training for
   leadership among projects and various other topics covered under
   Maternal and Child Health.

